# Agent workflow (mandatory)

## Before finishing a task that changes code

1. **Run linters** and fix all reported issues. Do not leave the workspace in a failing lint state.
2. **Restart local dev stands yourself** after changes that affect runtime (backend and/or frontend): kill listeners on `localhost:3000` and `localhost:3001`, then start `pnpm nx run backend:serve` and `pnpm nx run frontend:dev` again in the background from the repo root. Do this **without asking** the user to restart—treat it as part of handing off the task. Skip only if the user has explicitly asked not to touch running processes in this session.

## Lint & format commands (repository root: `pnpm nx …`)

| Scope | Command |
|--------|---------|
| **All projects** | `pnpm nx run-many -t lint --all` |
| **Affected only** | `pnpm nx affected -t lint` (needs git base; optional when appropriate) |
| **Backend (Go)** | `pnpm nx run backend:lint` — golangci-lint |
| **Frontend** | `pnpm nx run frontend:lint` — ESLint |
| **Frontend formatting** | `pnpm nx run frontend:format:check` (or `pnpm --dir apps/frontend exec prettier --check .` — то же дерево, без Nx); fix: `pnpm nx run frontend:format:fix` |
| **Orval (OpenAPI → React Query)** | Regenerate: `pnpm nx run frontend:orval`. Drift check (must match committed output): `pnpm nx run frontend:orval:check` — run when changing `apps/backend/docs/swagger.json` or `apps/frontend/orval.config.ts` / mutator. |
| **Kiosk (Rust)** | `pnpm nx run kiosk-desktop:lint` — `cargo clippy` |

`shared-types` and `ui-kit` Nx `lint` targets are placeholders (echo only); real checks are `tsc` via `build` when you change those packages.

## Tests (when behavior changes)

- Backend: `pnpm nx run backend:test`
- Frontend: `pnpm nx run frontend:test`

## Restart API + Next.js (default local ports)

After backend and/or frontend code changes that require a running process to pick up new code or config (including migrations, env, routes), **run the restart yourself**—even if you are unsure whether the user still has dev servers open:

```bash
lsof -tiTCP:3000 -sTCP:LISTEN | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null
lsof -tiTCP:3001 -sTCP:LISTEN | xargs kill -9 2>/dev/null
sleep 1
```

Then start again in the background from repo root: `pnpm nx run backend:serve`, then `pnpm nx run frontend:dev` (short delay between starts is fine).

## Principles

- Run commands yourself; do not only suggest that the user run lint or restart servers.
- **Dev stands:** proactively restart API + Next.js after relevant edits; do not end the turn with “please restart” unless the user opted out of restarts.
- Prefer `nx run-many -t lint --all` before handing off a multi-area change.
- If you only touched one app, you may scope lint to that project to save time, but run the full matrix before merge-ready work.
